100.description: The server has received the request headers and the client should proceed to send the request body.

101.description: The requester has asked the server to switch protocols and the server has agreed to do so.

102.description: The server is currently processing the request, but has not yet completed.

201.description: The request has been fulfilled and a new resource has been created.

202.description: The request has been accepted for processing, but the processing has not been completed.

203.description: The request was successful but the enclosed payload has been modified from that of the origin server's 200 OK response by a transforming proxy.

204.description: The server has successfully fulfilled the request and there is no additional content to send in the response payload body.

205.description: The server has fulfilled the request and desires that the user agent reset the 'document view', which caused the request to be sent, to its original state.

206.description: The server is delivering only part of the resource due to a range header sent by the client.

207.description: The message body that follows is an XML message and can contain a number of separate response codes, depending on how many sub-requests were made.

208.description: The members of a DAV binding have already been enumerated in a previous reply to this request, and are not being included again.

226.description: The server has fulfilled a request for the resource, and the response is a representation of the result of one or more instance-manipulations applied to the current instance.

300.description: The request has more than one possible response.

301.description: The requested resource has been assigned a new permanent URI and any future references to this resource should use one of the returned URIs.

302.description: The requested resource resides temporarily under a different URI.

303.description: The response to the request can be found under a different URI and should be retrieved using a GET method on that resource.

304.description: The requested resource has not been modified since the last time it was accessed.

305.description: The requested resource must be accessed through the proxy specified in the Location header.

306.description: This status code is no longer used, but was previously reserved.

307.description: The requested resource has been temporarily moved to the URL specified in the Location header.

308.description: The requested resource has been permanently moved to the URL specified in the Location header.

400.description: The request could not be understood or was missing required parameters.

401.description: Authentication failed or user does not have permissions for the requested operation.

403.description: The requested resource is forbidden and cannot be accessed.

404.description: The requested resource could not be found but may be available in the future. Subsequent requests by the client are permissible.

405.description: The HTTP method used in the request is not supported for the requested resource.

406.description: The requested resource is not capable of generating a response matching the list of acceptable values defined in the request's headers.

407.description: The client must first authenticate itself with the proxy.

408.description: The server timed out waiting for the request.

409.description: The request could not be completed due to a conflict with the current state of the resource.

410.description: The requested resource is no longer available at the server and no forwarding address is known.

411.description: The server requires a Content-Length header to be included in the request.

412.description: The server does not meet one of the preconditions specified in the request headers.

413.description: The request is larger than the server is willing or able to process.

414.description: The URI provided in the request is too long for the server to process.

415.description: The server cannot process the request because the media type is not supported by the server or has been disabled for this resource.

416.description: The server cannot provide the requested range of the resource; that is, the requested range extends past the end of the resource.

417.description: The expectation given in the Expect request header field could not be met by at least one of the inbound servers.

418.description: This code was defined in 1998 as one of the traditional IETF April Fools' jokes, in RFC 2324, Hyper Text Coffee Pot Control Protocol, and is not expected to be implemented by actual HTTP servers.

421.description: The server is not able to produce a response for this request due to a client error; for example, if the request is malformed or invalid.

422.description: The request was well-formed but was unable to be followed due to semantic errors.

423.description: The resource that is being accessed is locked.

424.description: The request failed due to a failure of a previous request.

426.description: The client should switch to a different protocol such as TLS/1.0, given in the Upgrade header field.

428.description: The origin server requires the request to be conditional.

429.description: The user has sent too many requests in a given amount of time.

431.description: The server is unwilling to process the request because its header fields are too large.

451.description: The server is denying access to the resource in response to a legal demand.

500.description: The server encountered an unexpected condition that prevented it from fulfilling the request.

501.description: The server does not support the functionality required to fulfill the request.

502.description: The server received an invalid response from an upstream server while attempting to fulfill the request.

503.description: The server is currently unable to handle the request due to a temporary overload or maintenance of the server.

504.description: The server did not receive a timely response from an upstream server while attempting to fulfill the request.

505.description: The server does not support the HTTP protocol version used in the request.

506.description: Transparent content negotiation for the request results in a circular reference.

507.description: The server is unable to store the representation needed to complete the request.

508.description: The server detected an infinite loop while processing the request.

510.description: Further extensions to the request are required for the server to fulfill it.

511.description: The client needs to authenticate to gain network access.
